text.tspan: Keldling Brew
This is made from organic Pilzner malt, organic
Hallertau Blanch hops and S-23 Dry Lager yeast.
The malt was mashed in 1° steps from 60°C to 78°C.
Malt and yeast gives it a yellow/golden color (~5 EBC).
The hops adds the bitterness (6.5% Alpha acids)
and some floral/fresh/fruity notes (~35 IBU).
The yeast makes it clear, dry and fresh. It contained
approx. 6% alchohol when bottled on the 20th of
February 2017.
“Competition is good for consumers for the simple reason
that it compels producers to offer better deals – lower prices,
better quality, new products, and more choice.” - Sir John
Vickers, former Chairman of the Office of Fair Trading, U.K.
Professor
